line_1: O Thou, who labour'st in this rugged mine,
line_2: May'st thou to gold th' unpolish'd ore refine!

line_1: May'st thou to gold th' unpolish'd ore refine!
line_2: O Thou, who labour'st in this rugged mine,

line_1: May each dark page unfold its haggard brow!
line_2: Doubt not to reap, if thou canst bear to plough.

line_1: Doubt not to reap, if thou canst bear to plough.
line_2: May each dark page unfold its haggard brow!

line_1: To tempt thy care, may each revolving night,
line_2: Purses and maces swim before thy sight!

line_1: Purses and maces swim before thy sight!
line_2: To tempt thy care, may each revolving night,

line_1: From hence in times to come, advent'rous deed!
line_2: May'st thou essay, to look and speak like Mead.

line_1: May'st thou essay, to look and speak like Mead.
line_2: From hence in times to come, advent'rous deed!

line_1: When the black bag and rose no more shall shade
line_2: With martial air the honours of thy head;

line_1: With martial air the honours of thy head;
line_2: When the black bag and rose no more shall shade

line_1: When the full wig thy visage shall enclose,
line_2: And only leave to view they learned nose:

line_1: And only leave to view they learned nose:
line_2: When the full wig thy visage shall enclose,

line_1: Safely may'st thou defy beaux, wits, and scoffers;
line_2: While tenants, in fee simple, stuff thy coffers.
